Cape Town - From the worst storm to hit Cape Town in 30 years to a carpet of snow over the Ceres mountains, South Africans would be forgiven for wondering what's next when it comes to the weather. Cold and icy conditions are set to continue in the Western Cape and the rest of the country for the remainder of the week. eNCA climatologist Annette Venter tells reporter Aarti Narsee what to expect in the video above. eNCA